        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 16 at 3:27PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elizabeth, or 31 miles southeast of Denver, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elizabeth, Kiowa, Ponderosa Park and Franktown.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
